# cursor-deck — core conventions

This is a Reveal.js deck template. Pure HTML + CSS, no build step.

## Stack rules

- **Don't introduce React, Vite, Next.js, MDX, TypeScript, or any
  bundler.** The zero-build setup is intentional and load-bearing for
  community contributors.
- **Don't add `npm install` dependencies** unless the user explicitly
  asks. `serve` is fetched on demand via `npx`.
- **Don't change Reveal.js options** (`Reveal.initialize({…})`) without
  applying the same change to both `template/` and
  `examples/cursor-nexo-security/`.

## Slide chrome — required on every slide

Every `<section>` must contain:

1. A `.chrome` div at the top with the Cursor logo and an `.eyebrow`
   label.
2. A `.footer` at the bottom with the org line + `NN / MM` counter
   (except the dark title and closer slides, which use a custom bottom
   block).
3. The right logo variant: `*_LIGHT.png` on `.slide`, `*_DARK.png` on
   `.slide.dark`.

When you add or remove a slide: **update the `NN / MM` counter on every
following slide.** And update the `MM` total on every slide.

## Two decks

- `template/` — the generic starter. Edit this.
- `examples/cursor-nexo-security/` — historical reference deck. Don't
  edit unless the user explicitly asks for a correction.

## Color and typography

Use CSS custom properties from `theme.css`. Never hardcode hex values
in slide content. See `theme-tokens.mdc` for the full list.
